  "prompt": "How can I reach Infosys Pocharam campus from Ameerpet?",
  "response": "Reaching Infosys Pocharam Campus from Ameerpet involves a combination of public transport and private options. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide:\n\n### 1. **By Bus and Metro:**\n   - **Step 1:** Take the Hyderabad Metro from **Ameerpet Metro Station** to **JBS Parade Ground Metro Station** (towards Raidurg).\n   - **Step 2:** From JBS Parade Ground, walk to **Jubilee Bus Station (JBS)**.\n   - **Step 3:** Board a bus from JBS to **Infosys Pocharam Campus**. Look for buses heading towards Pocharam or Ghatkesar and ask the driver to drop you at Infosys Pocharam.\n   \n   **Note:** Bus frequency may vary, so check schedules in advance.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **By Cab or Auto:**\n   - Book a **cab (Ola/Uber/Rapido)** or hire an **auto** directly from Ameerpet to Infosys Pocharam Campus. This is the most convenient option but will be costlier than public transport.\n   - The distance is approximately **40 km**, and the journey takes around **1-1.5 hours**, depending on traffic.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **By Two-Wheeler or Private Vehicle:**\n   - Take the **Rajiv Rahadari (Outer Ring Road)** from Ameerpet towards **Ghatkesar**.\n   - Follow signs for **Pocharam** or **Infosys Campus**.\n   - The campus is well-marked and easy to locate on Google Maps.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Train Option (Not Recommended):**\n   - You can also take a train from **Secunderabad Railway Station** to **Ghatkesar Railway Station** and then hire a cab or auto to Infosys Pocharam. However, this is less convenient due to limited train schedules.\n\n---\n\n### Tips:\n- Check **traffic conditions** before traveling, especially during peak hours.\n- If using public transport, confirm bus timings or metro schedules in advance.\n- Carry cash for autos or buses, as digital payment options may not always be available.\n\nLet me know if you need more details!",
